  <h2>Why Does My Cat Shed So Much — and Can Brushing Actually Help?</h2>
  <p>Indoor cats shed year-round because artificial lighting disrupts their natural seasonal cycles. The loose fur they can't reach accumulates in the undercoat, either ending up on your furniture or getting swallowed during self-grooming and forming hairballs. Regular brushing is the only real solution, but most tools either irritate sensitive skin or get abandoned because the cat won't tolerate them.</p>
