  <h2>The Right Way to Use a Deshedding Brush Without Hurting Your Cat's Coat</h2>
  <div style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:1.25rem;margin:1.25rem 0;">
  <div class="how-to-step"><div class="step-number">1</div><div class="step-text"><strong>Fill and activate the steam</strong><p>Add a small amount of water to the reservoir, press the steam button, and wait 10-15 seconds before bringing it near your cat. Never apply steam to the face or ears.</p></div></div>
  <div class="how-to-step"><div class="step-number">2</div><div class="step-text"><strong>Brush in the direction of fur growth with light pressure</strong><p>Start at the neck and work toward the tail. Let the weight of the brush do the work — pressing harder doesn't collect more fur. Avoid the belly unless your cat allows it.</p></div></div>
  <div class="how-to-step"><div class="step-number">3</div><div class="step-text"><strong>Remove fur and clean after each session</strong><p>Peel collected fur off the silicone bristles in one motion. Rinse under warm water. Fold the handle flat for storage. Do this 3-4 times a week for best results.</p></div></div>
